# Subject line (50 characters max)
#

# Body (72 characters per line)
#
# - Use imperative mood ("add feature" not "added feature")
# - Focus on WHY, not WHAT
# - Reference issues with: fixes #123, relates to #456
# - Separate multiple concerns into different commits
#
# Commit Types:
# feat:     A new feature
# fix:      A bug fix
# docs:     Documentation changes
# style:    Code style changes (formatting, etc)
# refactor: Code refactoring without feature changes
# test:     Adding or updating tests
# chore:    Build process, dependencies, tooling
# perf:     Performance improvements
# ci:       CI/CD configuration changes
#
# Example:
# feat: add dark mode toggle to settings
#
# Users can now customize the application theme.
# Implements design system from #123.
